## Development

### Code Style

This project follows Rust standard conventions:
- Use `cargo fmt` to format code
- Use `cargo clippy` to catch common mistakes
- Write tests for new functionality

### Release Builds

```bash
just release           # Build optimized release binaries
{% if cli_module == 'enabled' and 'rust' in cli_languages %}
# CLI binary will be at: target/release/{{ package_name }}
{% endif %}
{% if api_module == 'enabled' and 'rust' in api_languages %}
# API binary will be at: target/release/{{ package_name }}-api
{% endif %}
```

Release builds are optimized for size and performance with:
- LTO (Link-Time Optimization)
- Stripped symbols
- Single codegen unit
- Size optimization

